body_text:

#
 
\xe3\x80\x82


I want to sublet the main bedroom in California Street, Mountain View. The location of the room is only 3 minutes walking time to San Antonio shopping center, where a lot of different shops such as Walmart, Target, CVS are there. The bus 22, 34, 35 or Caltrain can be taking if you want to go to Stanford University.

It is an individual room (183 ft2) with an individual bathroom inside the bedroom. Kitchen and living room is shared with others.

The rent is $1350/month for single person only, including all the utility fee.

The Lease is at least 3 months, long term is preferred. The tenant should join the lease, and pay the nonrefundable application fee ($35) to the leasing office.

The room is available now. And the lease can be at least extended to Nov. of 2017.

Current roommates include a visiting scholar at Stanford University and a software engineer in the company nearby, both are male.

If you are interested, please contact me at Tel: 
 
or Email:

title: March-April sublet furnished room utilities included
body_text:
b'Furnished room available in 3bdr/2bath apartment for 2 months sublet(March and April)
March will be prorated. April is $900.
Lease can be extended for another year if you are the right fit.
This is great for commuters too.

Two other roommates are mature males
Washer/dryer is in the apartment.

Room is furnished. It comes with full size bed, night stand, lamp, and desk with a chair.
All utilities including high speed internet are included.
Bathroom is shared with one other roomate
The complex is nice. It has gym and swimming pool.

Room is only 10min walking distance from Pleasanton downtown and 10 min drive from BART.
The room is aprx 150sq.ft and goes for $900 plus $250 deposit'

The rent is $1350/month for single person only, including all the utility fee.

title: 1 small bdrm in 2 bdrm apt
body_text:
b"Hi so a little bit about the apt. Its a house thats been converted into a 2 seperate apts. Im on the ground floor with 2 bdrms, bathroom, kitchen, living room etc. The rent is 900 a mo. The utilities will be included (water,pg&e, garbadge) I only have internet in my room so if you want it it would have to come out of your own pocket (sorry). I also don't have a house phone as well. I have a washer/dryer that I bought and I'd  be willing to share and work out some kind of washing sched with you. You will have off street parking. No visitor parking though street prkg is kinda sucky. The prking in the back is super small and for the tenants only. Sorry no sleep overs of any kind, visiting is fine as long as theres prior notice pls. You will have kitchen privileges and I have a fridge that I can make room for your groceries. Out of courtesy for my neighbors and its also apt policy as well, no loud noise after 10. I have a couple and a 3yr old that live above me. They are rarely home so its fairly quiet... 

What Im looking for...
Female preferred, sorry guys no offense. Pls have a job,be able to show proof of income.
At least a 30 day notice to vacate if after your not feeling it will work for you.
Would love it if you didn't smoke, but if you do it has to be off the property  (like literally across the street)(brokers rules not mine)
Sorry no pets of any kind. (Brokers rules)
Be clean. I mean no one is perfect but hey strive to be tidy so I'm not cleaning up after you.
No party girls pls. Im not super loud or have loads of ppl come over. What you do outside of the house off the property is your business. 
Being a people person is a nice plus, because I am :o) I will do a meet and greet away from the house first just to be formal to see if theres good vibes. And would like it if my g/f can accompany me.

A bit about me....
So first off, out the gate, I am a lesbian and yes I  have a g/f. She doesn't live with me but she will come over every once in a while. If you are cool with this and like minded,awesome, if you aren't but won't  have a prob living with a les ok, cool and I have respect for everyone's choices, as I hope you will too.  Im 36, I  have my own car and I work crazy hours. Im super friendly, virgo need I say more. I do enjoy a little drink every now and again but you will never see me crawling the floor drunk :o) I'm mostly a home body. I just moved into this house about 6 months ago soooo I have boxes and stuff in places that I'm trying to clear up and out of the way. If I've left anything out or you have questions pls feel free to ask. ;o)
The tie breaker.....
Soooo ultimately I'm not trying to be here long, my g/f and I are planning on moving to Oregon in about 6 to 7 months (god willing) give or take and if things work out with you and I, I can try and transfer the apt into your name when I get ready to leave. Or I can just give you a heads up b4 I get ready to leave so you can start looking and do your own thing. All in all, having someone help with the rent would be awesome,So I can save for my big move. Some of the things I've said can be negotiable within time. Pls. Just bear with me as this will be my first time renting out this room to a stranger... thanks again for reading all my babble and happy hunting! \xf0\x9f\x98\x86"

title: Seeking roommate
body_text:
b"1 bedroom available in a 2bed/1bth apartment in Campbell. 

Apartment is located about 3 blocks from Downtown Campbell if you like to enjoy the bars and good restaurants. 

Apartment was recently remodeled therefore I was the first to live here. 
Kitchen with dishwasher, granite counter tops and new stove 
Bathroom is to die for, granite sink with vanity mirror like. 
Bedroom has a nice size closet. 
Livingroom is amazing size and has two closets that would be shared. 
One parking spot and plenty of visitor parking in the back of the building.
Laundry room is available and coin operated, pretty nice and clean for a shared laundry room .

Just moved in December 2016, there is no furniture in the living room or kitchen beside the basic dishes and etc. 
Seeking for a responsible, reliable, professional, respectful person.
Someone that would take as much responsibility as I and treat this place like our sanctuary. 

A bit about myself: 
I'm a 25year old professional female, working as an HR Administrator who works all day and comes home to work or relax depends on the day.
Very open minded and friendly as well as trustworthy.
I'm very responsible when it comes to bills and rent. 
Weekends I usually work or hang out with my family but there are days where I'll just stay in bed. 

Ideally I'm seeking a Female, between 23-30 years old 
Has a stable job/ income 
Easygoing, clean and drama free 

Don't really mind overnight guests but also don't want someone or someone different every night. We can work out the kinks. 
Also don't mind having friends over as long as they are respectful and get heads up. A simple text would work. 

I know this is a long shot but the person on the lease with me couldn't pay rent anymore so she's moved out. 
Need someone for April 1st, available to move in sooner as well, mid to late March.

All will be split evenly: Rent, utilities, home supplies, etc. 

If you are interested please text me or email."

title: Tracy Roommate Wanted ASAP!!!!
body_text:
b"Hi! 

I am in desperate need of a roommate to rent a house. I moved to Tracy but I have to move again

I prefer a male roommate just because I know I get along better with men as roommates. I just know myself and wouldn't want to make home life miserable.

 I do have a 8 month old daughter, she is amazing and smiles and laughs all day. I am gone through the day and commute over an hour to work so I will never be home. My daughter will be awake for maybe an hour or two when I get home and then go to bed (she sleeps through the night). 

I work in property management and have a great income, just with a baby and being a single parent I can't seem to keep up with the market on houses. I have found several options that would work to have privacy for both of us. I would like to find someone as soon as possible because I cannot stay at my current place with the water being as bad as it is. :[ 

Please call or text!!!

I put 1400 because that's what I can afford with utilities. We can find a pretty great house if both of us contribute 1000 to 1200"

title: Private Room In SSF
body_text:

We are looking for a housemate to share our comfortable 3 bedroom 2\xc3\x82\xc2\xbd bath home in a very quiet neighborhood. title: Room in gated community 3 min walk to Bart (欢迎中国
body_text:
b'Hi, 

We have a room in a 3bed 2bath apartment located in Hayward City Centre available for rent. Move-in date is in Mid April ( yet to be confirmed with the girl moving out)

About the place:
*3 mins walk to bart station
*washer and dryer in the house
*carpeted floor mats in rooms
*walk-in closet
*2 big windows and sunny
*access to gym, spa and swimming pool
*gated community 
*street parking
*shared bathroom and full kitchen
*not furnished (desk only)
*mid size room ~200 sq ft
*shared utilities ~$60/mo (including water, pg&e, internet)
* Rent $730

Link to the community:
http://www.essexapartmenthomes.com/california/san-francisco-bay-area-apartments/hayward-apartments/city-centre

About the roommates (all in late 20s): 
Me (female): work in SF full time and am never home on weekends; staying in the master room; 
Xin (female): staying in the room next to yours; work part time and go to school full time; rarely at home;
Longyan (male): staying in the living room; full time student at AAU; heavy video game player;

About you:
Ideally Chinese speaking (so we can communicate well); 
Please be clean and respectful;
Full time student or has a full time job;
No overnight guests;


Please text or email me

 
Vivian


Thank you for reading!'

title: Private clean room, Convenient Area, Easy Transportation - Sunset
body_text:
b'We offer a clean room near all kind of transportation, park, shops, banks and cafes within walking distance. 

Some roommates are on medical rotations, internship or students and they are clean and drama free. 

They are young professional students from all over the world. All of them are male and we are looking for a male tenant to fit into the group.

It is fully furnished with a bed, a desk and a chair. 

The room is very clean and secure. It has windows with sunlight. 

You will have a key to your room for privacy and a key to the front door.

$80 utilities for wireless internet access and the rest. 

Sorry no pets, DRAMA, party and visitor(s). We are a smoke, alcohol, drug and party free house. 

We are looking for a male tenant. If interested, please email to us and tell us a bit about yourself.'

title: Quiet room w/private bath on nice court - Near PA/MV Hi Tech
body_text:
b"Furnished quiet room on first floor with private bathroom in beautiful two story mediterranean home. On quiet court in the Barron Park neighborhood with convenient access to Stanford and public transportation on El Camino Real. Ideal for working professionals, Stanford students and internships; close to high tech companies in Mountain View and Palo Alto.

Rent includes:
- utilities
- wi-fi
- washer/dryer
- kitchen (dedicated space in refrig/freezer & cupboard :)

Live in a house that feels like a home with easy going, no drama professional couple, and an awesome yellow lab. Two very nice professionals rent rooms upstairs. My name is Michael and I work in high tech PR; my wife Cece works in retail. Minimum three month lease with first, last and small deposit. Available Saturday, April 22nd.

Looking for no drama, pleasant and clean person. The house arrangement works great for everyone - we plan to keep it that way :). If that's you, please contact us."

title: Room For Rent (ONE MALE ONLY)
body_text:
b"We have 1 room available for rent in our 4 Bedroom and 3 Bathroom modern style single family home in a quiet neighborhood in Milpitas. The room is available for move in RIGHT NOW.

DESCRIPTION OF ROOM:
Living area: 12' x 10' 
Closet: 6.5' x 2'

*Shared bathroom 
*Central heating and AC
*Utilities: water, garbage, PG&E, and wifi internet access

COMMON AREAS:
*Laundry Room

AMENITIES:
* Easy access to Highways 680, 237, and 880
* Close to: Great Mall, Milpitas Square, McCarthy Ranch, Milpitas Town Center and high Tech companies
* Nearby groceries: Safeway, Lucky's, Save Mart, Nob Hill, Ocean Supermarket, Lion Supermarket, Ranch 99 and Marina Market
* Nearby stores: CVS, Walgreens, Rite Aid, Wal-Mart, and Target

LOOKING FOR:
* responsible, clean, and easygoing MALE 
* one person per room
* no cooking or microwave food heat up only
* no smoking, alcohol, drugs nor pets
* No overnight guests

* Lease Agreement minimum 6 months, after 6 months, lease becomes month-to-month

* Deposit $300


CONTACT INFORMATION: 
Phil 
 
 Please text or email for address.

Thank you"

title: Beautiful  2 bdrm berkeley share
body_text:
b"I am looking for a fabulous roommate to share my gorgeous 2 bd/1 ba North Berkeley home starting April or May for short or longer term. 2-10 Minute walk to Ohlone Park, Trader Joe's, and North Berkeley Bart. 

I am 40's, athlete, spiritual, business owner, professional performing artist, Berkeley native with 6 years in NYC.  

I am looking for a person who is grounded, personal growth committed, financially stable, has great credit, and is direct, integritous, and has strong communication skills.  Please be warm and kind. 

Please be comfortable with community, guests in the house, and a warm family feeling, but also enjoy quiet and a zen environment.  

I prefer someone who has an office where they work outside the home most days, but can be flexible for the right person.  Please be neat and aware of cleanliness in the common spaces ( but not a perfectionist), and be willing to take part in a cleaning schedule and the occasional house meeting.  No smokers (not allowed on property) or substance-users.

The rent is $1200 per month, all utilities and household basics included. 1st, last, and a $600 deposit is needed to move in, as well as a credit report, pay stub, and 3 personal and 3 work references.

The room is large, has carpet, and also has a big closet.  It is furnished.  The bathroom is shared.

There is a lovely friendly cat that lives here, and there are no other pets allowed. The place has a dishwasher, washer/dryer, lovely light, a new remodeled kitchen, and wonderful landlords who live upstairs.   

Please send me an email to introduce yourself,  and let me know if you are a fit based on the above. Thank you so much! 

Blessings, Bekka"

title: 1 large room, furnished and conveniently located in Silicon Valley
body_text:
b"1 furnished bedroom in a 4-bedroom single home. We live in a quiet, tree-lined neighborhood that is conveniently located. It is within walking distance to grocery stores, restaurants, and local bus stops. Freeway entrances to 85, 237, 101, and 280 are only a few minutes away - great for getting to Silicon Valley companies (like Google, Yahoo, Apple) and traveling around the Bay Area. Looking for more? Downtowns Sunnyvale and Mountain View (as well as Caltrain) are 5-10 minute drives away.

Available now! The bedroom has a closet and is furnished with a bed, desk, and a lamp. Wifi is available throughout the home. Light-cooking only, no smoking, and no pets.

The room is available for rent for $1100 per month, on a month-to-month contract. 

Looking for someone that is easy-going, clean, and respectful of everyone's living space. 

If you're interested, please inquire and tell me more about yourself. If it sounds like a good match, I will contact you.

Photos available upon request. Thank you!"

title: Room Available in a Wonderful House!
body_text: b'Room available as a single or double. $760 for the room, plus utilities. For sublet May 1st through September 30th. The house has two bedrooms and one bathroom and a shed. Clawfoot bathtub in a separate room from the toilet. Has a washer and dryer. You would share the house with three other wonderful young artist women, current UCSC students/recent grad. House has a piano and record player! Great location on the 19, 16 and 15 bus routes. Space for car in the driveway.'

title: Sweet Apt - great location
body_text:
b"This is a single room, great location on 24th Street and Folsom.

Three other nice housemates. We all tend to do our own things, with varying schedules but always friendly with the occasional catch up over dinner.

1 bathroom, furnished bedroom and kitchen.

You won't find a better deal in the city.

I am only moving out as I'm going to live with my girlfriend."

title: Beautiful master bed room in Nob Hill
body_text:
b"-Move-in date: April 27, 2017 - May 1st (can be flexible)
-Rent: $1600/month
-Utilities (Water, Gas, Electric, Internet): ~$60/month depending on usage (never really over that though)

-Available room is the master bedroom in a 2 bed/1 bath home in Nob Hill with converted living room. There are 3 total bedrooms and girl in the master bedroom is moving out so we are looking for a great new roommate! Living room has doors so everyone has their own privacy! Master bedroom has large closet, large windows, natural sunlight, and beautiful crown moldings!
-The lease is 1 year and month-to-month thereafter and a security deposit is required.
-There is free laundry in the basement with designated time slots for each unit
-The home comes with lots of storage space
-Brand new stainless steel appliances
-There is a central heating system which is rare for SF!
-Wood floors throughout the home!
-We're only 4 blocks to Polk Street, 1 block from Trader Joe's, and very close to public transportation!
-Street parking only 

**We're looking for an early to mid-20's female who is responsible, clean, and can pay bills on time. You like to have fun but not bring the party home. You must also provide pay stubs/proof of employment and have a credit check.**


If you're interested, please write an email with the following:
-Age
-Occupation
-Desired move-in date and if it's flexible
-What type of living situation you are looking for
-What you like to do for fun
-Link to your Facebook/LinkedIn page

Sorry no couples or pets are permitted!"

title: Master Bedroom Fully Furnished
body_text: b'Beautiful and very clean master bedroom in a three bedroom, three bath town home. Room is fully furnished and includes all bedding, towels, floor mats, queen bed, dressers, lamps, etc. Bedroom includes full private bath, walk-in closet, and TV. Quiet, safe, and clean home close to public transportation, downtown, and shopping. $75 monthly utilities fee includes electric, garbage, water, Internet, directv, and washer dryer. First month plus $600 security/cleaning deposit to move in April 1st. No smoking, drugs, or pets. Ok to call.'

title: Private Room Private Bath in a 2bd2ba Top Floor Apt
body_text:
b"Move in date very flexible as i am looking for a compatible roommate to share my 2bd2ba top floor unit in the inner sunset. Room for rent is the master bedroom with private bathroom and walk in closet. Washer dryer in building, secured apt building with property manager living in one of the units. Building has no smoking and no pets policy so I appreciate a roommate that can respect that. Rent comtrolled. 

This is for 1 person only. I'm looking for a clean, respectful, a good communicator, and a responsible person for either short term or long term. Having occasional guests are OK as long as it doesn't interupt or disturb the other person. I believe that my place is also your place so I really don't like imposing rules besides that shoes off the apartment for sanitary purposes. Hehe

About me: 27yo gay male, RN and works full time for the city hospital. My schedule is every other weekend off 7am to 330pm. On my free time I like traveling, going out to dinner, watching movies, hiking and spending my time with my friends and family. I'm a previous marathoner having ran 1 full marathon and 20+ half marathons (planning on getting back to it).

Rent is 1850 plus half of the bills (pge and internet only about 50dollars a month) I don't have cable. Water and garbage included in the rent.

Parking space in the building optional for 150 a month.

Please tell me a little bit about yourself. Let me know if you're looking for short term or long term.

Pics are of the apartment unit prior to getting filled with some furnitures back in August. Will update with up to date photos tomorrow. 

B"

title: $950 Room with private bath for rent - Dublin Ranch Golf Course
body_text:
b'Located on the beautiful Dublin Ranch Golf Course. Close to Fallon Gateway shopping center and Hacienda Crossings Shopping Center with terrific specialty shops, service, and restaurants.

Close to  BART station.

*Utility Fees included
*Private bathroom
*free super-fast wifi
*Free Uverse service
*Washer and dryer
*Water filter with Reverse Osmosis for clean and healthy drinking water
* Share kitchen - access to 6 stove burners and oven, microwave, dish washer, refrigerator
*Furnished bed or bring in own
*Ample parking in front of house


$35 credit check fee with application. No pet. No smoking. 
Must be quiet and respectful

Required to Move-in: First Month Rent + 1 Month (last Month Rent) with $350 Security Deposit

Please email or text me if you are interested.'

title: Room for rent in House On the water
body_text: b'Large room for rent in Discovery bay. House is on the water, great views. Room has large closet with shelves, bathroom is semi private. (Guest bathroom, but no one uses shower) Includes use of laundry, driveway parking, and light use of kitchen is ok. Must be mature and professional, clean up after yourself, and most importantly pay rent On Time. House is 420 friendly, and there is 1 dog. Lease is month to month, $500 deposit. Rent is $800 per month utilities included. \nThanks! :)'

title: $950 Hayward hills room for rent, near CSUEB, pets ok!
body_text:
b'Hi everyone,
I'm a 27 year old female working full time at south San Francisco. Currently, I'm looking for a single roommate, female preferred, and either students or working professionals are OK to me. But you should able to provide a proof that you can afford this room. I'm a very easy going person, and willing to do a lot of outdoor activities with friends. Looking for someone who is clean and understands the responsibilities of living fairly with another person. I'm not thinking to rent the living space out, so, basically just two of us living here.  Perfect for CSUEB students, close to campus. No drama queen and drug accepted, and you can host party or invite overnight friends, as long as you notify me ahead of time. Smoking is ok but outside or balcony.
\xc3\xa2\xc2\x80\xc2\xa2 This is a 2 bedrooms, 1.5 bathroom apartment, your room will be 10'3"x10'10", with nice closet. And we will share one bath tub. Room will be available at March 21st. 
\xc3\xa2\xc2\x80\xc2\xa2Rent Price: $950 Deposit: $350, application fee will be $38 as a requirement. We will separate all the utilities including water, PG&E, internet, average to $90-100.

\xc3\xa2\xc2\x80\xc2\xa2 Bonus: you can bring your pets to live with you, with additional deposit $250 and pet rent $50. I have two extremely lovely and friendly doggies, so if they can get along with each other, will be great. 
\xc3\xa2\xc2\x80\xc2\xa25 min drive from Cal State East Bay  Both Hayward and Castro Valley BART stations are nearby 15 min. 
\xc3\xa2\xc2\x80\xc2\xa2This community has a recently remodeled gym, swimming pool, spa, laundry rooms. . ...

Since this apartment is not available right now, but i could ask office to show you a similar property to see if you like it or not. Also, you are welcomed to visit my dogs before you decide to move in. Currently, I am living in the same community, can tell you this is a well managed and safe community. Here is the community's website http://www.essexapartmenthomes.com/california/san-francisco-bay-area-apartments/hayward-apartments/city-view

Please feel free to contact me, with a brief introduction about yourself would be appreciated.

Thank you for your time!'
